        {
          "question": "<p>Answer the following question :</p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n\t<li>What is a ball and socket joint?</li>\r\n\t<li>Which of the skull bones are movable?</li>\r\n\t<li>Why can our elbow not move backwards?</li>\r\n</ol>",
          "id": 72537,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 19404,
              "solution": "<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n\t<li>The rounded end of one bone fits into the hollow space of the other bone, such kind of joint is called ball and socket joint. The ball and socket joint allows movements in all directions.</li>\r\n\t<li>In the skull, only the lower jaw is movable.</li>\r\n\t<li>Our elbow can not move in the backward&nbsp;direction, because the elbow has a hinge joint that allows only a back and forth movement.</li>\r\n</ol>"
            }
          ],
